      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To fix your bathroom sink's constant drip, you'll need a wrench, a screwdriver, and a new washer. First, turn off the water supply to prevent any accidental leaks. Then, remove the handle by unscrewing it with the screwdriver. Once the handle is off, you'll see a small screw holding the washer in place. Remove the screw, pull out the old washer, and replace it with the new one. Finally, reassemble the handle and turn the water back on. If you're having trouble with the old-style handle, it might be easier to replace the entire faucet. Check with your local hardware store for the specific part you need. Good luck, and remember to always be careful when working with plumbing.",
