      "content": "If your handle is stuck, you might want to try some penetrating oil to loosen it. Apply the oil around the base of the handle and let it sit for a few minutes before attempting to turn it again. If the handle still won't budge, you may need to remove the entire faucet, which can be a bit more involved. The constant drip could also be caused by a worn-out valve seat, a faulty cartridge, or even a cracked supply line. These issues are more complex to fix and may require a plumber's expertise. If you're feeling adventurous, you can try disassembling the faucet to inspect the valve seat or cartridge. Just be sure to have a clean workspace and take your time. If you're unsure, it's always best to consult a professional plumber. Remember, a little bit of patience and the right tools can go a long way in tackling plumbing issues. Good luck!",
      "source": "target",
